BY OBESITY LEVEL - The highest level of average forced expiratory volume was observed from obese BMI people, and it decreased respectively with BMI level. - The highest level of asthma was observed from normal BMI people. The lowest was observed from underweight people(less than 1 percent).

BY SMOKE GAS EXPOSURE LEVEL - The highest level of average forced expiratory volume was observd from people with the second hand smoke exposures. The lowest FEV was observed from double exposure people. - The highest level of asthma was observed from people with gas stove exposure, which take up 9.6 percent.
